  "text": "Based on Nei's genetic distance coefficient [CITATION_1] , a dendrogram was obtained using NJ cluster analysis. The 67 accessions were divided into 2 groups and 4 subgroups based on the genetic diversity of the endo-PG gene (Figure 3 ). The main cluster \"I\" included the subgroups I-1 and I-2. Subgroup I-1 included 26 accessions -10 accessions with NMF fruit phenotypes, presenting a mixed distribution with different adherence levels to the stone in the dendrogram.",
